{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-jsx","path":"/react/scheduler/docs/guides/localization/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"react-scheduler---localization\"><a href=\"#react-scheduler---localization\" aria-label=\"react scheduler   localization permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>React Scheduler - Localization</h1>\n<p>The React Scheduler provides an API that allows you to format dates and localize messages.</p>\n<p><strong>Format Dates</strong></p>\n<p>Scheduler UI plugins can display dates that are formatted depending on the locale. To specify the locale, assign one of the <a href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5646\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">supported formats</a> to the <a href=\"../reference/scheduler.md\">Scheduler</a> component's <code class=\"language-text\">locale</code> property.</p>\n<p><strong>Localize Messages</strong></p>\n<p>Most UI plugins have the <code class=\"language-text\">messages</code> option that accepts localized messages.</p>\n<h2 id=\"basic-setup\"><a href=\"#basic-setup\" aria-label=\"basic setup permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Basic Setup</h2>\n<p>The following example demonstrates how to localize the Scheduler by specifying the <code class=\"language-text\">messages</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">locale</code> properties.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-localization/locale\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>\n<h2 id=\"customize-date-formatting\"><a href=\"#customize-date-formatting\" aria-label=\"customize date formatting permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Customize Date Formatting</h2>\n<p>To customize how dates are formatted in a component, <a href=\"./fundamentals.md#customize-the-appearance\">override the component</a> and set the <code class=\"language-text\">formatDate</code> property to a function that formats dates. The following example illustrates these actions. Note that in this example, the <a href=\"https://momentjs.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Moment.js</a> library is used to work with dates.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"scheduler-localization/custom-formatting\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>","fields":{"technology":"react/scheduler","section":"docs"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"react/scheduler/docs/guides/localization/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3159585216","3662068265"]}